This Privacy Policy describes how Wallet GO: Expense Tracker ("we", "our", or "the App") handles your information. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our practices.

1. Information We Collect

Wallet GO is designed with a privacy-first approach. All your financial data is stored locally on your device only.

Financial Data: Transactions, budgets, goals, accounts, and bills you create are stored exclusively in a local database on your device. This data is never transmitted to any server.
Preferences: App settings such as currency selection, theme preference, biometric lock preference, and profile name are stored locally on your device using Android DataStore.
Biometric Data: If you enable biometric lock, authentication is handled entirely by your device's operating system. We do not access, collect, or store any biometric data.
2. Information We Do NOT Collect

We do not collect personal identification information (name, email, phone number)
We do not collect or access your bank account, credit card, or any real financial account information
We do not track your location
We do not use analytics or tracking SDKs
We do not transmit any of your data to external servers
We do not share, sell, or rent your data to any third party
We do not display personalized or behavioral advertisements
3. Data Storage and Security

All data is stored locally in an encrypted SQLite database on your device.
The App supports biometric authentication (fingerprint/face unlock) as an additional layer of security, using Android's BiometricPrompt API.
Your data remains on your device and is protected by your device's built-in security features.
4. Permissions

The App may request the following permissions:

Biometric / Fingerprint: To enable optional app lock via biometric authentication.
Notifications: To send bill payment reminders that you configure.
Camera: For potential future receipt scanning features (not used to collect data).
Internet: Required for potential future cloud backup features. Currently, no data is transmitted over the internet.
Boot Completed: To reschedule bill reminders after device restart.
5. Data Retention and Deletion

Your data persists on your device for as long as the App is installed.
You can delete individual transactions, budgets, goals, accounts, or bills at any time from within the App.
Uninstalling the App permanently deletes all associated data from your device.
You can clear all app data at any time via Android Settings > Apps > Wallet GO > Clear Data.
6. Children's Privacy

Wallet GO is a general-purpose expense tracking tool. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13. The App does not require account creation or any personal information to function.

7. Third-Party Services

Wallet GO does not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising, or data collection services. The App operates entirely offline and independently.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.

